h2 Using Icons
p.-text Icons can be added via Web component, SVG or Web Font. Choose the method that best suits your projects needs.

h3 SVG & JS Method
p.-text SVG based implementations provide better semantics, accessibility, rendering, and reliability. Place the following script in your projects footer to use this method.
.-mb--2
  :code(lang='html')
    <script src="https://assets.ctl.io/chi/2.0.0/chi-icons.js"></script>
p.-text Then to render an SVG icon, apply the class <code>chi-icon</code> to an element. Next, add an <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> tag and specify the id of the icon you wish to use in the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code>'s href:
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    chi-icon(icon="atom")
  ul#example-default.chi-tabs.-ml--3
    li.-active
      a(href='#webcomponent-default') Web component
    li
      a(href='#svg-default') SVG
    li
      a(href='#webfont-default') Web font
  #webcomponent-default.chi-tabs-panel.-active
    :code(lang="html")
      <chi-icon icon="atom"></chi-icon>
  #svg-default.chi-tabs-panel
    .chi-tab__description
      | To render an SVG icon, apply the class <code>chi-icon</code> to an element. Next, add an <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> tag and specify the id of the icon you wish to use in the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code>'s href:
    :code(lang="html")
      <div class="chi-icon">
        <svg aria-hidden="true">
          <use xlink:href='#icon-atom'/>
        </svg>
      </div>
  #webfont-default.chi-tabs-panel
    .chi-tab__description
      | Web Font based implementations offer the widest browser support,
      | fastest rendering speed, and require no additional script or stylesheet.
    :code(lang="html")
      <i class="chi-icon icon-atom"></i>

h2 Sizes
p.-text By default, icons render at 16x16px (<code>sm</code>).
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .chi-grid.-align-items--end
      each size in ['xs', 'sm', 'sm--2', 'sm--3', 'md', 'lg', 'xl', 'xxl']
        div.-p--2.-m--1
          chi-icon(icon="atom", size=size)
          p.-text.-text--center= size
  .example-tabs.-pl--2
    ul#example-sizes.chi-tabs
      li.-active
        a(href='#webcomponent-sizes') Web component
      li
        a(href='#svg-sizes') SVG
      li
        a(href='#webfont-sizes') Web Font
  #webcomponent-sizes.chi-tabs-panel.-active
    .chi-tab__description
      | Use the size attribute to render icons larger or smaller:
      | <code>xs</code>, <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, <code>lg</code>, <code>xl</code>, <code>xxl</code>.
      | Two alternate small values are available for specific app scenarios. Use <code>sm--2</code>
      |  for displaying 20px icons within a 40px container (e.g. large button), and <code>sm--3</code> for displaying
      | 24px icons within a 48px container.
    :code(lang="html")
      <!-- -xs : 12x12px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="xs"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -sm : 16x16px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="sm"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -sm--2 : 20x20px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="sm--2"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -sm--3 : 24x24px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="sm--3"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -md : 32x32px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="md"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -lg : 64x64px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="lg"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -xl : 96x96px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="xl"></chi-icon>
      <!-- -xxl : 128x128px -->
      <chi-icon icon="atom" size="xxl"></chi-icon>
